1
00:00:06,027 --> 00:00:08,779
[siren wailing]

2
00:00:10,239 --> 00:00:12,575
[somber music playing]

3
00:00:13,492 --> 00:00:15,036
[respirator puffing]

4
00:00:17,371 --> 00:00:19,081
[breathes heavily]

5
00:00:19,749 --> 00:00:21,917
[reporter] Special Operation Unit
Sergeant Kim Cheon-gyu

6
00:00:22,001 --> 00:00:23,961
has passed away from the explosion.

7
00:00:24,628 --> 00:00:28,507
The lead investigator, Min Gang-yong of
the Major Crimes Investigation Division,

8
00:00:28,591 --> 00:00:32,136
was also severely injured and has been
transferred to a nearby hospital.

9
00:00:35,056 --> 00:00:37,016
12 CASUALTIES IN GANGNAM HOTEL EXPLOSION

10
00:00:46,108 --> 00:00:47,777
[machine whirring]

11
00:00:50,863 --> 00:00:51,781
[clunks]

12
00:00:52,865 --> 00:00:55,117
[somber music continues]

13
00:01:00,623 --> 00:01:01,499
[phone buzzing]

14
00:01:01,582 --> 00:01:04,543
-[man] Did you check the patient's vitals?
-[woman] I'm on my way.

15
00:01:05,044 --> 00:01:08,255
[cell phone buzzing]

16
00:01:08,339 --> 00:01:09,632
LEE WOO-JEONG
WOO-JIN

17
00:01:09,715 --> 00:01:12,051
[cell phone buzzes]

18
00:01:12,134 --> 00:01:13,260
Hello? Yes?

19
00:01:13,344 --> 00:01:16,138
You're on a group call.
It's Woo-jeong. Are you there?

20
00:01:16,639 --> 00:01:18,224
-Yes.
-[Woo-jin] I'm here, Woo-jeong.

21
00:01:18,307 --> 00:01:19,850
Where are you both right now?

22
00:01:19,934 --> 00:01:22,937
Mr. Moon brought me to a repair shop
that he knows well.

23
00:01:23,521 --> 00:01:25,689
We have the girl
who drugged Min-beom with us.

24
00:01:26,857 --> 00:01:27,858
Gun-woo, where are you?

25
00:01:29,860 --> 00:01:32,738
Gang-yong got hurt. I'm at the hospital.

26
00:01:33,572 --> 00:01:34,824
Gang-yong got hurt?

27
00:01:34,907 --> 00:01:36,826
-[Mr. Moon] Where is he?
-How? What happened?

28
00:01:37,368 --> 00:01:40,204
[Woo-jeong] Woo-jin, wait a minute.
Could you please hold for a moment?

29
00:01:40,704 --> 00:01:44,166
-Yes.
-Gun-woo, how bad is everything?

30
00:01:45,334 --> 00:01:46,418
Gang-yong,

31
00:01:47,962 --> 00:01:50,214
he's being given a CT scan right now.

32
00:01:50,297 --> 00:01:51,882
[Woo-jeong] What condition is he in?

33
00:01:55,344 --> 00:01:56,554
He's unresponsive.

34
00:01:57,972 --> 00:02:00,558
-He's not responding.
-Shit! Fuck!

35
00:02:02,768 --> 00:02:05,896
Then could you please stay where you are
and let me know if anything changes?

36
00:02:05,980 --> 00:02:07,356
Will you do that for me?

37
00:02:08,816 --> 00:02:09,692
Of course.

38
00:02:09,775 --> 00:02:13,362
[Woo-jeong] I'll head over to the repair
shop then. Woo-jin, give me the address.

39
00:02:13,946 --> 00:02:15,531
[Woo-jin] I'll send it right away.

40
00:02:21,537 --> 00:02:23,539
[tense electronic music playing]

41
00:02:49,523 --> 00:02:51,901
BLOODHOUNDS 2

42
00:02:52,526 --> 00:02:54,528
[tense music playing]

43
00:03:11,754 --> 00:03:13,214
[sighs] Stay here.

44
00:03:13,297 --> 00:03:14,715
Yes, of course.

45
00:03:16,008 --> 00:03:18,969
[Director Kang] When your father told me
what happened, I planned to see you.

46
00:03:19,053 --> 00:03:20,012
I'm sorry I'm late.

47
00:03:21,263 --> 00:03:22,598
What is it you need?

48
00:03:22,681 --> 00:03:23,849
I need a specialist.

49
00:03:26,143 --> 00:03:27,353
Is that what you want?

50
00:03:27,436 --> 00:03:29,647
Yes. I need a person to be killed.

51
00:03:30,940 --> 00:03:32,566
This the one who drugged you?

52
00:03:34,818 --> 00:03:36,195
The one who ordered it.

53
00:03:38,781 --> 00:03:39,823
[sighs]

54
00:03:41,533 --> 00:03:42,910
Why were you drugged?

55
00:03:43,786 --> 00:03:45,246
You did something?

56
00:03:49,041 --> 00:03:49,917
[exhales]

57
00:03:55,798 --> 00:03:58,634
I have an employee that cleans things.

58
00:03:59,218 --> 00:04:01,387
I can put him on this one, but

59
00:04:02,805 --> 00:04:04,390
think it over carefully.

60
00:04:05,766 --> 00:04:07,309
If the guy deserves it.

61
00:04:08,018 --> 00:04:10,104
I will return the favor any time.

62
00:04:11,313 --> 00:04:12,273
All right.

63
00:04:13,524 --> 00:04:14,775
The job will get done.

64
00:04:15,776 --> 00:04:17,319
I'm thankful for this.

65
00:04:17,820 --> 00:04:18,946
[music fades]

66
00:04:19,029 --> 00:04:22,157
-[Mr. Moon] Tell us! Who ordered the job?
-Oh, shut up!

67
00:04:22,241 --> 00:04:24,451
Oh, fuck!

68
00:04:26,537 --> 00:04:28,998
I've had enough.
I'm not in any mood for your games.

69
00:04:29,081 --> 00:04:32,251
So tell me, who did it, huh?
Who ordered it?

70
00:04:32,918 --> 00:04:34,211
Get close to me, okay?

71
00:04:35,921 --> 00:04:36,922
[sighs]

72
00:04:37,881 --> 00:04:39,091
Tell me.

73
00:04:39,800 --> 00:04:40,926
Get closer.

74
00:04:41,010 --> 00:04:43,554
This is stupid fucking shit.
Tell me! Who is it?

75
00:04:43,637 --> 00:04:45,681
No, because it's a secret.

76
00:04:48,225 --> 00:04:49,393
Hmm.

77
00:04:52,229 --> 00:04:54,606
Hey, come on. Tell me the secret.

78
00:04:56,108 --> 00:04:56,942
What?

79
00:04:58,402 --> 00:05:00,571
-[Mr. Moon screams]
-[Woo-jin] Oh shit! Let go of him!

80
00:05:00,654 --> 00:05:02,906
-Oh fuck! What the hell?
-[Gi-na laughs]

81
00:05:02,990 --> 00:05:05,451
-[Mr. Moon] You're fucking crazy!
-[Gi-na laughs]

82
00:05:05,534 --> 00:05:06,493
[Mr. Moon] Let me go.

83
00:05:06,577 --> 00:05:08,579
-[Gi-na laughs]
-No, don't do that. No.

84
00:05:08,662 --> 00:05:09,538
Oh, whoa!

85
00:05:09,621 --> 00:05:11,582
-Fucking let go of me! Let go!
-Control yourself.

86
00:05:11,665 --> 00:05:13,667
Hold it together. Mr. Moon.

87
00:05:14,168 --> 00:05:15,502
[groans] All right.

88
00:05:15,586 --> 00:05:19,631
-[Mr. Moon exhales]
-[Gi-na laughs]

89
00:05:19,715 --> 00:05:22,551
It's all right. It's okay.
Let go. I'm fine.

90
00:05:22,634 --> 00:05:26,680
[Gi-na laughs]

91
00:05:26,764 --> 00:05:27,598
Having a laugh?

92
00:05:27,681 --> 00:05:30,017
Yeah, it's so funny. It's so great.

93
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:32,436
Yeah, it's funny. It's so fun.

94
00:05:32,519 --> 00:05:35,647
Oh, my stomach hurts. [laughs]

95
00:05:35,731 --> 00:05:37,816
-Wow, young lady.
-[Gi-na sighs]

96
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:39,860
Look at you, with your pretty legs.

97
00:05:40,444 --> 00:05:42,029
You must be popular.

98
00:05:42,112 --> 00:05:44,698
But what if I break them?

99
00:05:45,199 --> 00:05:47,034
It won't take much to break your knees.

100
00:05:47,117 --> 00:05:48,285
[tense music playing]

101
00:05:48,369 --> 00:05:50,662
They'll never heal
and you won't walk again.

102
00:05:52,790 --> 00:05:54,041
Is that what you need?

103
00:05:54,625 --> 00:05:56,585
Hmm? [laughs]

104
00:05:58,337 --> 00:06:01,048
-[whimpers]
-[Mr. Moon] I'm ready.

105
00:06:01,131 --> 00:06:03,759
[tearfully] Please don't do that.

106
00:06:03,842 --> 00:06:08,597
I'm so very frightened.
You won't do that, will you?

107
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:11,767
-I'm so very sorry. Please don't do that.
-So then just tell me. It's okay.

108
00:06:11,850 --> 00:06:16,146
Please, go ahead. Tell me, who was it?
Stop crying. Just tell me. [chuckles]

109
00:06:16,230 --> 00:06:18,190
-[music stops]
-[mocking] "Just tell me."

110
00:06:18,273 --> 00:06:20,984
[Gi-na laughing]

111
00:06:21,068 --> 00:06:23,570
You fucking idiot!
You're a fucking asshole.

112
00:06:23,654 --> 00:06:25,030
-Stupid shithead.
-Fuck you!

113
00:06:25,114 --> 00:06:29,034
-[Sun-bo] No! Don't let her get to you!
-Let go of me! She needs a lesson!

114
00:06:29,118 --> 00:06:31,245
-[Gi-na laughs]
-[Mr. Moon] Fucking hell!

115
00:06:32,579 --> 00:06:34,581
You're asking to get hurt.

116
00:06:34,665 --> 00:06:35,958
[tense music playing]

117
00:06:36,041 --> 00:06:37,334
You want to be punished?

118
00:06:37,418 --> 00:06:38,669
Mm.

119
00:06:39,670 --> 00:06:41,255
I like it very hard.

120
00:06:41,797 --> 00:06:43,382
How will you punish me?

121
00:06:44,967 --> 00:06:49,138
-Fuck.
-[laughing]

122
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,306
[laughs]

123
00:06:51,390 --> 00:06:52,433
Hit me.

124
00:06:52,933 --> 00:06:56,353
Do it. [chuckles] Go on, do it.

125
00:07:02,985 --> 00:07:04,153
[sighs]

126
00:07:07,030 --> 00:07:09,324
The guy said if I open up here

127
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:12,161
and say who paid for it,

128
00:07:12,661 --> 00:07:14,746
then he will cut off my feet,

129
00:07:15,622 --> 00:07:18,417
and sell me to be trafficked
in Southeast Asia.

130
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:23,505
You would keep your mouth shut too.

131
00:07:26,008 --> 00:07:27,301
[exhales]

132
00:07:29,219 --> 00:07:30,137
[grunts]

133
00:07:33,557 --> 00:07:34,892
[cell phone buzzes]

134
00:07:35,809 --> 00:07:38,103
LEE WOO-JEONG

135
00:07:40,647 --> 00:07:42,316
[Woo-jin] Woo-jeong. I'm here.

136
00:07:52,618 --> 00:07:53,952
Are there any updates on the girl?

137
00:07:54,036 --> 00:07:57,164
We threatened her,
but she's not saying anything to us.

138
00:07:57,664 --> 00:08:01,251
She's a very tough one.
She almost bit Mr. Moon's ear off.

139
00:08:01,335 --> 00:08:03,170
Did Mr. Moon do anything to her?

140
00:08:03,253 --> 00:08:06,924
Not at all. No one hurt her.
No one touched her. We made threats.

141
00:08:07,007 --> 00:08:08,133
[exhales]

142
00:08:08,675 --> 00:08:12,888
So, is she the one who contacted Mr. Min
and gave him the info of the hotel?

143
00:08:12,971 --> 00:08:13,972
Is that what happened?

144
00:08:14,056 --> 00:08:16,767
No. Tae-yeong hacked her phone
and found it that way.

145
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:17,851
Ah.

146
00:08:17,935 --> 00:08:22,105
Woo-jeong, could you then go inside
and maybe see her yourself?

147
00:08:23,273 --> 00:08:25,776
Sure. Please tell me who she is.

148
00:08:26,276 --> 00:08:29,112
Oh, come on. Just one cigarette.

149
00:08:30,155 --> 00:08:32,783
You're all such fucking tight-asses!

150
00:08:32,866 --> 00:08:34,326
All sorts of tactics. Damn it.

151
00:08:34,409 --> 00:08:35,327
-Mr. Moon.
-Yes?

152
00:08:35,911 --> 00:08:37,955
-[Woo-jeong] Hello.
-[Mr. Moon] Oh, you came.

153
00:08:38,038 --> 00:08:41,667
Woo-jeong, welcome.
Well, I can't get through.

154
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,711
-You might be able to reason with her.
-Sure. I will try speaking with her.

155
00:08:44,795 --> 00:08:45,796
Good luck.

156
00:08:56,139 --> 00:08:57,641
Who said you could sit?

157
00:09:05,941 --> 00:09:08,485
-Fuck off, you disgusting ass!
-[grunts]

158
00:09:16,827 --> 00:09:19,121
Will you go fuck off?!
What's wrong with you?!

159
00:09:19,204 --> 00:09:21,206
-Fuck this, seriously.
-Ah, don't do it!

160
00:09:24,293 --> 00:09:26,336
Is it okay if I sit here?

161
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:30,716
[chuckles derisively]

162
00:09:32,759 --> 00:09:33,802
[Gi-na sighs]

163
00:09:42,769 --> 00:09:46,189
Will you… work things out?

164
00:09:47,274 --> 00:09:49,610
I'd appreciate it
if you could cooperate with us.

165
00:09:50,611 --> 00:09:51,528
[spits]

166
00:09:55,616 --> 00:09:57,409
I can wait longer if you need.

167
00:09:59,745 --> 00:10:03,123
Ah, this fucking sucks!
Who brought this guy?

168
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:05,876
[sighs]

169
00:10:06,418 --> 00:10:07,336
Hey.

170
00:10:08,211 --> 00:10:10,130
Just go fuck yourself already.

171
00:10:10,213 --> 00:10:13,842
The police got info from your phone
and were able to raid the hotel.

172
00:10:15,093 --> 00:10:16,303
Did you know that?

173
00:10:17,971 --> 00:10:20,682
They probably think
you leaked the information

174
00:10:20,766 --> 00:10:22,726
and they're looking for you right now.

175
00:10:24,811 --> 00:10:26,521
You know how they'll hurt you.

176
00:10:27,230 --> 00:10:29,399
They won't forgive you for the breach.

177
00:10:30,025 --> 00:10:33,737
They'll never believe you,
no matter how much you try and explain.

178
00:10:33,820 --> 00:10:36,698
They'll track you down
and they'll get their revenge.

179
00:10:36,782 --> 00:10:41,078
So if you cooperate with us…
we can make sure you'll be safe.

180
00:10:41,161 --> 00:10:44,831
How can you find a way
to protect me from them?

181
00:10:45,415 --> 00:10:49,127
You see, if we catch them first, there'll
be no way for them to try and hurt you.

182
00:10:49,628 --> 00:10:52,756
That'll be how we do it.
The next step would be a reduced sentence.

183
00:10:52,839 --> 00:10:55,467
Are you fucking stupid
or out of your mind?

184
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:58,053
Why would I go to jail?
I have nothing to confess. Got it?

185
00:10:58,136 --> 00:11:00,055
Gi-na? This is the deal.

186
00:11:00,931 --> 00:11:02,766
If you cooperate with us…

187
00:11:06,269 --> 00:11:08,522
we can help you
out of the situation safely.

188
00:11:10,399 --> 00:11:11,358
Trust me.

189
00:11:14,069 --> 00:11:14,945
[exhales]

190
00:11:24,871 --> 00:11:25,706
[sighs]

191
00:11:32,379 --> 00:11:33,463
Let me go.

192
00:11:34,047 --> 00:11:34,881
The tape.

193
00:11:39,845 --> 00:11:41,304
Sun-bo, you've got a knife?

194
00:11:41,388 --> 00:11:42,806
Woo-jeong, think it through.

195
00:11:51,481 --> 00:11:52,399
[music fades]

196
00:12:00,991 --> 00:12:02,325
[Woo-jeong] Thank you, Sun-bo.

197
00:12:10,959 --> 00:12:13,086
The person who hired me is Lee Man-bae.

198
00:12:13,795 --> 00:12:14,921
You know where he is now?

199
00:12:15,005 --> 00:12:16,423
[tense music playing]

200
00:12:16,506 --> 00:12:18,341
Why would I know that?

201
00:12:18,842 --> 00:12:21,303
I only meet him when he has a job for me.

202
00:12:21,386 --> 00:12:22,971
[Woo-jeong] How long have you known him?

203
00:12:24,264 --> 00:12:27,142
It's been three years
when he gave me the first job.

204
00:12:27,225 --> 00:12:28,643
What did you do for him then?

205
00:12:28,727 --> 00:12:30,395
[laughs]

206
00:12:30,479 --> 00:12:33,857
Hey. For crying out loud,
why would I tell you?

207
00:12:33,940 --> 00:12:35,025
Such a bitch.

208
00:12:35,108 --> 00:12:36,026
[Gi-na scoffs]

209
00:12:37,527 --> 00:12:40,405
Then can you say the names
of who Lee Man-bae's working with?

210
00:12:41,072 --> 00:12:43,950
How would I know? I've met him once.

211
00:12:44,034 --> 00:12:48,038
Why don't you give us some more
information about how he operates?

212
00:12:51,124 --> 00:12:52,000
Hey, you there.

213
00:12:56,338 --> 00:12:57,756
[groans]

214
00:12:58,507 --> 00:13:00,300
She has a lot of tactics.

215
00:13:22,155 --> 00:13:25,826
A while ago,
we drank so much we blacked out.

216
00:13:25,909 --> 00:13:30,664
That's when he told me he used to do work
for the National Intelligence Service.

217
00:13:32,165 --> 00:13:35,335
But he left that job
because he had some troubles with money.

218
00:13:35,836 --> 00:13:37,546
He couldn't find another job,

219
00:13:37,629 --> 00:13:41,299
so he started connecting people
with the ones from the service.

220
00:13:41,383 --> 00:13:43,343
He seemed honest about that.

221
00:13:43,844 --> 00:13:46,888
But who knows for sure?
He's not exactly the open type.

222
00:13:48,014 --> 00:13:49,349
You have his contact info?

223
00:13:51,017 --> 00:13:52,811
It changes every time he calls.

224
00:13:53,311 --> 00:13:55,272
He never answers when I call.

225
00:13:56,189 --> 00:13:59,651
So we correspond via text, and I'd wait.

226
00:14:04,155 --> 00:14:05,991
What was the drug
you put in Min-beom's drink?

227
00:14:06,074 --> 00:14:08,535
-[tense music continues]
-Four-eyes.

228
00:14:08,618 --> 00:14:09,744
Yeah?

229
00:14:09,828 --> 00:14:11,454
Bring my bag here.

230
00:14:38,064 --> 00:14:40,150
Will you help us meet with Lee Man-bae?

231
00:14:42,944 --> 00:14:44,070
[sighs]

232
00:14:46,698 --> 00:14:48,533
I'd get fucked then.

233
00:14:51,286 --> 00:14:52,579
[Woo-jin] Gi-na.

234
00:14:53,163 --> 00:14:54,998
We're in the same position.

235
00:14:56,082 --> 00:14:58,835
You can only live if we catch them.

236
00:15:00,712 --> 00:15:03,298
Oh, damn this to hell.

237
00:15:06,384 --> 00:15:07,469
[Gi-na sighs]

238
00:15:10,472 --> 00:15:13,266
It's already so late. Tomorrow, I will.

239
00:15:13,350 --> 00:15:14,309
[Sun-bo exhales]

240
00:15:14,976 --> 00:15:16,478
[Mr. Moon chuckles]

241
00:15:16,561 --> 00:15:18,271
Fine. We'll bring you to the hotel.

242
00:15:18,355 --> 00:15:19,940
It's where we are.

243
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,108
Your place is too dangerous.

244
00:15:22,609 --> 00:15:23,777
[scoffs]

245
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,862
[music intensifies]

246
00:15:36,539 --> 00:15:37,457
This way.

247
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:41,336
[lock beeps]

248
00:15:48,218 --> 00:15:49,260
[beeps]

249
00:15:56,267 --> 00:15:57,227
[music fades]

250
00:15:57,310 --> 00:15:58,478
[door handle rattles]

251
00:15:59,020 --> 00:16:00,355
[sighs]

252
00:16:04,401 --> 00:16:05,402
[lock beeps]

253
00:16:07,404 --> 00:16:09,280
-Gun-woo, you're here?
-[Woo-jeong] Hello.

254
00:16:09,364 --> 00:16:10,281
[door closes]

255
00:16:15,453 --> 00:16:17,664
When did you get back from the hospital?

256
00:16:18,373 --> 00:16:19,624
Are you okay?

257
00:16:21,459 --> 00:16:23,253
The doctor said I should go home.

258
00:16:29,426 --> 00:16:30,427
How's Gang-yong?

259
00:16:33,430 --> 00:16:35,098
He's still in the ER.

260
00:16:38,143 --> 00:16:39,561
He's still unconscious.

261
00:16:40,437 --> 00:16:41,688
So he's the same.

262
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:50,405
How are you? Did you get hurt? You okay?

263
00:16:52,699 --> 00:16:53,658
You know,

264
00:16:55,493 --> 00:16:56,995
I've been thinking about it.

265
00:16:58,913 --> 00:17:00,123
I've thought it over.

266
00:17:00,623 --> 00:17:01,833
I can't stop thinking…

267
00:17:05,378 --> 00:17:06,546
that it's my fault.

268
00:17:09,966 --> 00:17:11,301
That all of it's my fault.

269
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:14,012
No, it's not. It's not at all.

270
00:17:14,095 --> 00:17:15,180
I should have just--

271
00:17:15,263 --> 00:17:17,640
[Woo-jin] Gun-woo,
listen to me, okay? Hey.

272
00:17:18,641 --> 00:17:20,685
Just please hear me. Gun-woo.

273
00:17:20,769 --> 00:17:24,189
Look at me. Okay? Hey, Kim Gun-woo.

274
00:17:28,651 --> 00:17:30,945
Min-beom, Gang-yong, and Mr. Moon,

275
00:17:31,905 --> 00:17:34,449
they were the ones who wanted to join us.

276
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:38,620
No matter what, they would have fought
with us anyway. You know that.

277
00:17:39,621 --> 00:17:41,664
We couldn't have stopped them
from joining us,

278
00:17:41,748 --> 00:17:44,042
and I understand why they've chosen to.

279
00:17:44,626 --> 00:17:46,211
They've got to fight with us.

280
00:17:46,711 --> 00:17:47,587
Why?

281
00:17:49,089 --> 00:17:50,423
Because you did.

282
00:17:50,507 --> 00:17:51,883
[poignant music playing]

283
00:17:51,966 --> 00:17:54,761
You risked your life
to fight for all of us.

284
00:17:55,720 --> 00:17:59,265
We're connected because of you, Gun-woo.

285
00:17:59,349 --> 00:18:00,767
You know that, right?

286
00:18:02,185 --> 00:18:04,354
If you're gone from our lives,

287
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:06,189
it's like…

288
00:18:08,316 --> 00:18:09,943
It's just not possible.

289
00:18:11,694 --> 00:18:14,739
So if you're in danger or in trouble,

290
00:18:15,323 --> 00:18:17,659
we all have to make sure to protect you.

291
00:18:18,368 --> 00:18:20,620
Look at Gang-yong and Mr. Moon
for example.

292
00:18:20,703 --> 00:18:22,163
A loan shark and a cop?

293
00:18:22,664 --> 00:18:25,083
They don't really fit together,
and yet, it's working out.

294
00:18:25,166 --> 00:18:26,876
Do you know why that is? Huh?

295
00:18:27,544 --> 00:18:28,586
Gun-woo,

296
00:18:29,838 --> 00:18:31,840
it's because of you…

297
00:18:34,259 --> 00:18:35,844
that we're a family.

298
00:18:37,178 --> 00:18:39,222
You're not the one causing problems.

299
00:18:40,348 --> 00:18:42,100
You're keeping us alive.

300
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:45,436
It's all because of you
that I'm here. [sniffs]

301
00:18:45,937 --> 00:18:48,022
[sniffles]

302
00:18:49,858 --> 00:18:50,942
[cries]

303
00:18:52,235 --> 00:18:54,612
-So, Gun-woo--
-[Gun-woo cries]

304
00:18:55,989 --> 00:18:57,782
[Woo-jin] You know our rule, right?

305
00:18:59,576 --> 00:19:00,660
Once a family…

306
00:19:00,743 --> 00:19:04,122
[cries]

307
00:19:04,205 --> 00:19:05,915
A… always family.

308
00:19:05,999 --> 00:19:07,417
And family?

309
00:19:10,420 --> 00:19:11,671
Keep each other

310
00:19:12,172 --> 00:19:15,675
s, s, safe… [crying]

311
00:19:15,758 --> 00:19:17,677
…until we die.

312
00:19:18,678 --> 00:19:23,057
Min-beom and Gang-yong will wake up soon.
They're really tough folks, you know.

313
00:19:25,143 --> 00:19:26,102
So then,

314
00:19:27,395 --> 00:19:29,939
you need to keep it together for them.

315
00:19:31,399 --> 00:19:32,483
Understand?

316
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:41,409
Mm-hmm.

317
00:19:41,993 --> 00:19:42,911
[sniffs]

318
00:19:48,750 --> 00:19:49,876
Feeling hungry?

319
00:19:52,837 --> 00:19:55,882
Woo-jeong, are you hungry?
Let's order some room service.

320
00:19:55,965 --> 00:19:57,634
Does a bunch of dishes, sound good?

321
00:19:58,301 --> 00:19:59,594
[Woo-jeong] Yeah, sounds great.

322
00:20:10,104 --> 00:20:11,356
[Woo-jin] What should we order?

323
00:20:13,316 --> 00:20:14,442
[Gun-woo] Woo-jin's right.

324
00:20:16,069 --> 00:20:17,195
I'll protect.

325
00:20:18,529 --> 00:20:20,990
I have to protect my family
with my own hands.

326
00:20:23,701 --> 00:20:24,744
[music fades]

327
00:20:27,121 --> 00:20:29,249
Hold on. This guy.

328
00:20:32,335 --> 00:20:36,422
He's got a crazy long reach.
He'll do well against Gun-woo. Next.

329
00:20:37,173 --> 00:20:38,383
Scroll down.

330
00:20:38,466 --> 00:20:39,634
[tense music playing]

331
00:20:39,717 --> 00:20:41,010
That one.

332
00:20:43,096 --> 00:20:46,182
[chuckles] I want this fucker.
He's a dirty fighter.

333
00:20:46,683 --> 00:20:48,559
The exact opposite of Gun-woo.

334
00:20:50,436 --> 00:20:52,814
Good shit. This'll be fun.

335
00:20:52,897 --> 00:20:53,982
[music fades]

336
00:20:58,069 --> 00:21:00,071
Hi, Tae-yeong. What is it?

337
00:21:01,281 --> 00:21:02,699
You've got to see this.

338
00:21:03,199 --> 00:21:06,661
It says this Thursday at 11 p.m.,
Gun-woo's going to fight.

339
00:21:07,912 --> 00:21:09,038
When did you see this?

340
00:21:09,539 --> 00:21:11,541
It was put up just right now.

341
00:21:13,501 --> 00:21:14,460
Where's Gun-woo?

342
00:21:14,961 --> 00:21:18,339
-[Woo-jin] He must have gone to exercise.
-They won't stop trying to get Gun-woo.

343
00:21:22,635 --> 00:21:24,637
[somber music playing]

344
00:21:28,725 --> 00:21:31,269
[monitor beeping steadily]

345
00:21:31,352 --> 00:21:33,396
[respirator pulsing]

346
00:21:41,946 --> 00:21:45,658
You have a linear fracture.
It's in the frontal bone area.

347
00:21:45,742 --> 00:21:46,868
Can you see it?

348
00:21:47,452 --> 00:21:48,494
Frontal bone?

349
00:21:49,912 --> 00:21:51,748
[doctor] This is a hairline fracture.

350
00:21:52,248 --> 00:21:54,834
The hematoma
is causing intracranial pressure.

351
00:21:54,917 --> 00:21:58,838
Until the pressure stops and returns
to normal, you need to get plenty of rest.

352
00:21:58,921 --> 00:22:00,298
I get it. Thank you.

353
00:22:00,381 --> 00:22:01,549
[doctor] Wait, hold on.

354
00:22:02,425 --> 00:22:04,052
There can be complications.

355
00:22:05,303 --> 00:22:07,263
I realize the complications.
Thanks for your time.

356
00:22:07,347 --> 00:22:09,265
We need to monitor it regularly.

357
00:22:09,349 --> 00:22:11,142
Thanks again. Have a good day.

358
00:22:11,225 --> 00:22:13,561
If the pressure increases,
you'll need surgery!

359
00:22:18,024 --> 00:22:18,900
[groans]

360
00:22:24,947 --> 00:22:27,367
-There hasn't been a response yet?
-Nope.

361
00:22:28,826 --> 00:22:32,747
Does Lee Man-bae normally
take a while to respond to you?

362
00:22:33,331 --> 00:22:35,291
It always changes.

363
00:22:37,126 --> 00:22:38,086
[coffee cup clinks]

364
00:22:38,836 --> 00:22:39,921
I want an iced coffee.

365
00:22:40,505 --> 00:22:41,839
[sighs]

366
00:22:50,139 --> 00:22:51,015
[lock beeps]

367
00:22:51,516 --> 00:22:52,475
[music fades]

368
00:22:54,769 --> 00:22:57,772
-[Woo-jin] Did you work out?
-Yeah, I went downstairs.

369
00:22:57,855 --> 00:22:59,399
I could have gone with you.

370
00:22:59,982 --> 00:23:02,735
You were sleeping deeply,
so I went by myself.

371
00:23:03,236 --> 00:23:04,320
[Woo-jin] Then tomorrow,

372
00:23:05,822 --> 00:23:07,156
we'll exercise together.

373
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:09,117
[somber music playing]

374
00:23:09,617 --> 00:23:10,535
Mm.

375
00:23:12,412 --> 00:23:15,248
[cell phone buzzing]

376
00:23:15,331 --> 00:23:17,208
GANG-YONG

377
00:23:20,586 --> 00:23:21,587
Hello?

378
00:23:22,088 --> 00:23:24,298
It's Gang-yong. Our champ, where are you?

379
00:23:25,425 --> 00:23:26,342
[exhales]

380
00:23:29,387 --> 00:23:31,013
[sighs] You okay?

381
00:23:31,764 --> 00:23:33,724
We've been all staying here at the hotel.

382
00:23:40,523 --> 00:23:41,524
-[Gang-yong] Hey.
-Hello.

383
00:23:43,234 --> 00:23:44,110
This way.

384
00:23:46,154 --> 00:23:47,363
Please, over here.

385
00:23:54,162 --> 00:23:55,163
Mr. Min!

386
00:23:55,997 --> 00:23:56,831
Hi there. All right.

387
00:23:56,914 --> 00:23:59,375
Mr. Min, you're fine?
You must be if you're out.

388
00:23:59,459 --> 00:24:01,919
-[Gang-yong] I've got to keep it easy.
-[Mr. Moon] Okay, good.

389
00:24:03,629 --> 00:24:04,839
Don't worry.

390
00:24:09,677 --> 00:24:11,679
[poignant music playing]

391
00:24:18,186 --> 00:24:19,103
Let's talk.

392
00:24:19,604 --> 00:24:20,438
Yes.

393
00:24:30,156 --> 00:24:31,908
Who could have told them
we were on our way?

394
00:24:35,203 --> 00:24:36,787
I thought about every detective

395
00:24:36,871 --> 00:24:40,249
and Special Operation Unit officers
who were at the scene.

396
00:24:41,125 --> 00:24:43,377
-I can't figure any of it out.
-[pensive music playing]

397
00:24:43,461 --> 00:24:47,131
The dead are the only ones
who aren't suspects right now.

398
00:24:47,840 --> 00:24:52,261
Maybe it was one of the hotel workers
I talked to.

399
00:24:52,345 --> 00:24:54,597
Someone at the front desk when I called.

400
00:24:56,015 --> 00:24:58,434
Then someone could have overheard
and leaked it.

401
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:03,314
Is this… what we need
to be focused on right now?

402
00:25:03,397 --> 00:25:07,026
Mr. Min, it would be logical
to look at Lee Man-bae now.

403
00:25:09,987 --> 00:25:11,155
We should move on our own.

404
00:25:11,989 --> 00:25:14,700
Everyone wants to get us, so

405
00:25:16,577 --> 00:25:17,828
we'll split up into two.

406
00:25:17,912 --> 00:25:20,289
Woo-jeong and I will follow Lee Man-bae,

407
00:25:20,373 --> 00:25:22,250
and Woo-jin and Gwang-mu will…

408
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:25,336
Oh, wait, I'm sorry.
No. Oh. No, my apologies.

409
00:25:25,419 --> 00:25:28,130
Ah, it's all right.
You don't have to be too formal with me.

410
00:25:28,214 --> 00:25:32,301
[chuckles] You both will handle
Yun Tae-geom's family.

411
00:25:32,385 --> 00:25:35,179
-We have no idea when he might show up.
-Yes.

412
00:25:35,263 --> 00:25:38,724
Mr. Min, we found the drug
used in President Hong's drink.

413
00:25:38,808 --> 00:25:40,393
We sent it to Forensic Service.

414
00:25:40,476 --> 00:25:43,312
[Gang-yong] Good.
When will the results come out?

415
00:25:43,396 --> 00:25:45,606
-[Woo-jeong] The day after tomorrow.
-[Gang-yong] Great.

416
00:25:45,690 --> 00:25:46,983
MARCH 13, 22:00
OLD BLDG. OF KOERI

417
00:25:50,319 --> 00:25:51,153
Gun-woo.

418
00:25:53,739 --> 00:25:54,865
-[Mr. Moon] You okay?
-Yes?

419
00:25:55,616 --> 00:25:57,159
Mr. Min wants to talk to you.

420
00:25:58,244 --> 00:25:59,453
Yes, sir?

421
00:26:00,705 --> 00:26:01,789
What do you wanna do?

422
00:26:03,708 --> 00:26:04,834
What?

423
00:26:05,418 --> 00:26:08,254
Uh, sir. Gun-woo can maybe stay here?

424
00:26:08,337 --> 00:26:10,590
It could help
if he stays in this building.

425
00:26:11,382 --> 00:26:14,093
Yes. The IKFC website had a post today

426
00:26:14,176 --> 00:26:17,930
that said Gun-woo was going to be
having a fight there this Thursday night.

427
00:26:18,431 --> 00:26:21,058
They'll do anything to get him to fight.

428
00:26:22,977 --> 00:26:25,646
Since there's tight security,
this place will be the safest.

429
00:26:27,815 --> 00:26:30,651
That's right. Yeah. It's for the best.

430
00:26:30,735 --> 00:26:35,114
Stay here for a bit longer.
We'll catch them, no matter what.

431
00:26:36,407 --> 00:26:38,326
Yes. Sir.

432
00:26:39,493 --> 00:26:41,078
We're in this together.

433
00:26:41,162 --> 00:26:42,246
Yes!

434
00:26:46,042 --> 00:26:48,961
-Good. One, two, three.
-[all] Let's do it!

435
00:26:50,254 --> 00:26:53,090
[electronic voice] Half. Call. Call, call.

436
00:26:55,259 --> 00:26:56,427
Half. Call.

437
00:26:57,428 --> 00:26:58,346
Half. Call.

438
00:27:01,932 --> 00:27:02,892
[Woo-jeong sighs]

439
00:27:03,559 --> 00:27:05,728
[video game coins rattle]

440
00:27:06,937 --> 00:27:08,230
MANJI: WHERE ARE YOU?

441
00:27:10,066 --> 00:27:11,317
[tense music playing]

442
00:28:04,328 --> 00:28:05,746
Shit, fuck.

443
00:28:13,170 --> 00:28:16,799
TARGET IN FRONT OF SOCIETY CAFE
ELIMINATE IMMEDIATELY

444
00:28:51,876 --> 00:28:53,878
-[dramatic music playing]
-[bike revving]

445
00:28:59,008 --> 00:29:00,259
[wheezes]

446
00:29:00,342 --> 00:29:02,136
[bystanders scream]

447
00:29:02,928 --> 00:29:04,054
No! Shit!

448
00:29:05,264 --> 00:29:07,516
Gi-na. Gi-na! Fuck.

449
00:29:09,477 --> 00:29:11,854
-Look at me, Stay with us.
-[Gang-yong] Someone's been hurt!

450
00:29:12,354 --> 00:29:15,608
674, Seoksan-dong, Jungang-gu.
Please hurry, please!

451
00:29:16,233 --> 00:29:18,235
[tense music playing]

452
00:29:25,284 --> 00:29:29,789
[grunting]

453
00:29:57,316 --> 00:29:58,400
[grunting]

454
00:30:01,153 --> 00:30:02,279
[grunting rapidly]

455
00:30:20,464 --> 00:30:21,674
[music fades]

456
00:30:24,093 --> 00:30:26,095
[somber music playing]

457
00:30:33,435 --> 00:30:35,354
Just going for a short walk.

458
00:30:59,879 --> 00:31:00,796
Follow me.

459
00:31:19,148 --> 00:31:21,775
[ominous music playing]

460
00:31:43,964 --> 00:31:44,840
Sit down.

461
00:31:45,925 --> 00:31:47,259
[tense music playing]

462
00:31:58,062 --> 00:32:02,066
It's good to see you in person.
To think we could have done this sooner,

463
00:32:03,442 --> 00:32:04,818
You stupid fucking asshole.

464
00:32:07,237 --> 00:32:09,281
I lost billions because of you.

465
00:32:10,366 --> 00:32:11,408
[sighs]

466
00:32:12,451 --> 00:32:13,410
Anyway.

467
00:32:16,038 --> 00:32:17,498
So tell me what makes you fight.

468
00:32:22,503 --> 00:32:23,337
Family?

469
00:32:26,382 --> 00:32:27,299
Friends?

470
00:32:31,178 --> 00:32:32,471
Those aren't forever.

471
00:32:32,972 --> 00:32:34,431
They'll leave in the end.

472
00:32:35,391 --> 00:32:38,102
It's money that stays. It's what'll last.

473
00:32:38,894 --> 00:32:41,689
Only the funds in your bank
are what protect you.

474
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:46,735
Money's what I fucking love.

475
00:32:48,445 --> 00:32:51,448
Because money stays with you,
never betrays you.

476
00:32:55,202 --> 00:32:57,621
Boxing was invented to make money.

477
00:32:58,622 --> 00:33:01,041
That's why the same weight-classed
fighters are matched,

478
00:33:01,125 --> 00:33:02,626
so they could last longer.

479
00:33:04,003 --> 00:33:06,130
Better for television, for ads.

480
00:33:06,213 --> 00:33:08,882
Boxers rest just enough
to stay alive for another one.

481
00:33:12,344 --> 00:33:15,973
These rules… were all made
to make a lot of money.

482
00:33:19,143 --> 00:33:20,352
So that's why

483
00:33:21,812 --> 00:33:23,355
you're gonna make money too.

484
00:33:24,481 --> 00:33:25,315
Got it?

485
00:33:31,196 --> 00:33:32,364
I don't want money,

486
00:33:33,490 --> 00:33:34,700
but let's do this.

487
00:33:43,584 --> 00:33:44,835
Well done.

488
00:33:46,712 --> 00:33:48,088
Then beat two assholes first.

489
00:33:48,797 --> 00:33:49,631
[scoffs]

490
00:33:52,009 --> 00:33:52,843
And…

491
00:33:55,220 --> 00:33:56,305
if you lose…

492
00:33:58,474 --> 00:34:00,225
your whole family will die.

493
00:34:00,309 --> 00:34:01,393
[inhales sharply]

494
00:34:10,736 --> 00:34:12,738
[tense music builds]

495
00:34:28,295 --> 00:34:29,379
[gasps]

496
00:34:32,925 --> 00:34:34,718
[knocking on door]

497
00:34:34,802 --> 00:34:36,428
-Gun-woo!
-Gun-woo?

498
00:34:36,512 --> 00:34:37,429
Anything wrong?

499
00:34:37,513 --> 00:34:40,349
-[Tae-yeong] We need to see Gun-woo.
-He just went out for a short walk.

500
00:34:40,432 --> 00:34:41,558
-[gasps]
-[So-yeon] He did?

501
00:34:43,519 --> 00:34:44,937
GUN-WOO

502
00:34:45,729 --> 00:34:49,358
[electronic voice] Phone is turned off.
You will be connected to voicemail.

503
00:34:56,740 --> 00:34:57,783
[music fades]

504
00:34:57,866 --> 00:34:59,660
[Tae-geom] Wrap these on your knuckles.

505
00:35:02,287 --> 00:35:03,622
This is how they fight here.

506
00:35:04,873 --> 00:35:06,333
I'll keep fighting the way I do.

507
00:35:06,834 --> 00:35:09,253
You won't win without these.

508
00:35:28,647 --> 00:35:30,315
[high-pitched ringing]

509
00:35:30,399 --> 00:35:32,442
Ow! [winces]

510
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:42,369
The IKFC debut of the WBC
super middleweight champion begins.

511
00:35:42,452 --> 00:35:46,415
Fighting out of Seoul, South Korea,
Kim "Scarface" Gun-woo!

512
00:35:46,498 --> 00:35:50,544
His opponent, with an IKFC record
of seven wins and three losses,

513
00:35:50,627 --> 00:35:51,962
Metal Mantis!

514
00:35:52,045 --> 00:35:56,008
